casebody.data:
Brenda R. WHITE, Plaintiff-Appellant,
v.
EDS CARE MANAGEMENT LLC, and Travelers Indemnity Company, Defendants-Appellees. SC: 158078
COA: 342657 Supreme Court of Michigan. October 11, 2018

Order

On order of the Chief Justice, the motion of plaintiff-appellant to waive filing fees is DENIED. In accordance with this Court's orders in No. 157197, White v. Southeast MI Surgical Hosp. , and No. 157199, White v. O.L. Matthews, M.D. , the plaintiff-appellant is not entitled to a waiver of the filing fee. The plaintiff-appellant must pay the filing fee within 28 days of the date of this order or the application for leave to appeal will be administratively dismissed.
